  "prompt": "How come people on Quora ask questions here, when they can get them on Google and why is Quora just a question/answer site, will it expand?",
  "response": "People often turn to Quora for several reasons, even when they could find information through Google:\n\n1. **Personalized Responses**: Quora allows users to ask specific questions and receive answers from a diverse range of contributors, including experts, enthusiasts, and individuals with personal experiences relevant to the question. This can provide more tailored and nuanced responses than a standard search engine might offer.\n\n2. **Community Engagement**: Quora fosters a sense of community, where users can engage in discussions, upvote answers, and interact with others who share interests. This interaction can be more satisfying and informative than simply reading articles or snippets on Google.\n\n3. **Quality Control**: Many users appreciate that Quora has a moderation system that aims to maintain quality and relevance. While Google retrieves vast amounts of information, not all of it is curated or trustworthy.\n\n4. **Diverse Perspectives**: On Quora, users can get answers from different angles and viewpoints, which may not be available in a simple search result. This diversity of opinion can enrich understanding.\n\nAs for the second part of your question about Quora being just a question/answer site and whether it will expand: \n\n1. **Focused Model**: Quora's model is specifically designed around Q&A, which helps it build a niche community. This focus allows for expertise in managing a platform specifically for knowledge exchange.\n\n2. **Potential for Expansion**: While Quora primarily functions as a Q&A site, it could expand in various ways\u2014like introducing new features, diversifying content formats (videos, podcasts), or integrating other community aspects (like forums or social networking).\n\n3. **Existing Changes**: Quora has already made some changes over the years, such as allowing blogs and posts, which can provide more depth and allow users to share longer-form content beyond just answers.\n\nOverall, while Quora\u2019s model is distinct, it has room for growth and adaptation based on user needs and interests.",
